        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"179006\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Man, I hope this was a special occasion.</p>\n<p>I suppose you could argue that any time you open a PYCM, it\u2019s a very special occasion, but I just checked at Wine-Searcher, and them sure ain\u2019t no $75 wines anymore.</p>\n<p>Every time I read a Burgundy note now, I think the same thing: How financially prudent is it to actually open and swallow this stuff?!?!?</p>\n<p>I don\u2019t even know that I could open bottles like these for Thanksgiving.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Assuming you meant financially prudent for you ?  <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/4/42a16863a8714da3c1604419e3eb9206bb87aa50.gif\" width=\"19\" height=\"27\" alt=\"[scratch.gif]\" title=\"scratch\" class=\"animated\">  <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/3/365d4ae6de5fe0cd9e7345760c12ceae1ed5e206.gif\" width=\"82\" height=\"55\" alt=\"[pillow-fight.gif]\" title=\"[pillow-fight.gif]\" class=\"animated\"><br>\nWhy the negativity on an otherwise great note on a great producer?</p>",
