        "created_at": "2022-05-04T11:51:07.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"179006\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"179006\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Btw\u2026didn\u2019t know Champs Gain(s)vineyard is in Chassagne AND Puligny? I have some Puligny Champs Gain\u2026was surprised to see it on this bottle.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Different vineyards I think. Nice wines and notes in any case!</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Yes, different vineyards! \u201cChamps Gain\u201d means re-cultivated field, denoting a site that was scrubland and then returned to viticulture.</p>",
